Definition: a highly lethal nerve agent used in chemical warfare
Example: a toxic liquid that penetrates the skin or lungs to disrupt the nervous system and stop respiration; in combat VX gas is deployed by detonating a container over the target area and can persist in the environment up to several weeks after release; VX gas is one of those things we wish we could disinvent
